Control Condition: iceMeasurement Section Codition: complete ice cverWeather Condition: clerWind Velocity: Calm Last BM Tie showed <0.003m change from established in BM#8. No GC required. CIC. Installed trail cam on home shore A-frame. Unexplained rise and fall back to regular trace prior to arrival. Began drilling ice at approximately 10:30. Stage appears to have resettled back down to 0.001m when DWL was obtained. Found tank empty but pressurized, purged to confirm clear. Could it be that the tank emptied just at that moment prior to our arrival? Mid-section

column14: Good x-section across from helipad. Open section on RB near home shore @ gauge/ under cableway. Price Metre chosen due to historically low SNR conditions at this site in December and January. Overflow slush throughout. Found tank empty, replaced with 1500lb tank. Purged clear & healthy. Reset while mmnt occuring, time constraints due to daylight availability/ long day ahead. Using DWL as MGH. DWL referenced to BM8: last BM Tie showed diff. from established elevation <0.003m, no GC required. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Cloudy , No Precipitation ,
column13: CIC at gauge and US/DS. No open leads.
column14: MEASUREMENT ASSUMED INVALID DUE TO QA/QC CONCERNS. Q VALUE VERY LOW FOR THIS TIME OF YEAR WHEN COMPARED TO HISTORICAL MEASUREMENTS. Fair measurement. Very low SNR (verified with FT2 at 0-1 SNR mid-section). Velocity intensity are approximately 55-66. I suspect the SPro is not measuring deeper velocities or depths very accurately. Left winter meter rods at hangar, unfortunate mistake. Only have aero rods which do not have a conventional metre hook-up. Bring SPro and winter metre to see if SNR values are any better next visit. Previous December FT2 measurement (2020) had 8 SNR which lead to think SPro would work well here. Not the case on this visit. CIC at gauge, approx 30cm ice. Ice edge surveyed @ 6.339m.  Mid-section
